com.ibm.team.process.common

Interface IAddElement


  • public interface IAddElement
    Represents the add-element child of a configuration-data-delta element.
    Since:
    4.0

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<IAddition> getAdditions()
      Get the list of IAddition that describe the elements to be added to the configuration-data.
      java.util.List<IProcessConfigurationElement> getPath()
      Get the list of IProcessConfigurationElement that describe where in the configuration-data tree this addition should take place.

    • Method Detail

      • getPath

        java.util.List<IProcessConfigurationElement> getPath()
        Get the list of IProcessConfigurationElement that describe where in the configuration-data tree this addition should take place.
        Returns:
        List of IProcessConfigurationElement, may be empty but not null.

      • getAdditions

        java.util.List<IAddition> getAdditions()
        Get the list of IAddition that describe the elements to be added to the configuration-data. In a valid configuration-data-delta section, the list will never be empty. In an invalid section, the list might be empty but should never be null.
        Returns:
        List of IAddition, may be empty but not null.
